(16, 1, '2010-09-22 17:14:06', '2010-09-22 17:14:06', '<p>The Church of Our Redeemer is located on Route 50 (John Mosby Highway) in the village of Aldie at <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=39518+John+Mosby+Highway,+Aldie,+VA&amp;sll=38.975075,-77.634737&amp;sspn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=39518+John+Mosby+Hwy,+Aldie,+Loudoun,+Virginia+20105&amp;ll=38.975225,-77.636969&amp;spn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;z=16">39518 John Mosby Highway ·  Aldie, VA 20105</a>. The church is 1 mile west of the traffic circle where Route 15 (north to Leesburg, south to Haymarket) and Route 50 (west to Middleburg, east to South Riding) intersect.  For directions, <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=39518+John+Mosby+Highway,+Aldie,+VA&amp;sll=38.975075,-77.634737&amp;sspn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=39518+John+Mosby+Hwy,+Aldie,+Loudoun,+Virginia+20105&amp;ll=38.975225,-77.636969&amp;spn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;z=16">click here</a> or look at the map below.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><IMG src=''/aldiechurch/images/directions.png''></IMG></p>\r\n<br />\r\n<p>From <strong>South Riding</strong>, head west on Route 50, past the three traffic circles. The church will be on your right.</p><br />\r\n<p>From <strong>Leesburg</strong>, head south on 15, turn right onto Route 50. The church will be on your right.</p>\r\n<p>From <strong>Haymarket</strong>, I-66, and points south, head north on 15, go 3/4 around the traffic circle onto Route 50 west. The church will be on your right.</p>\r\n<p>From <strong>Middleburg</strong> and points west, head east on Route 50, past Snickersville Turnpike, and through Aldie. The church will be on your left.</p>\r\n<p>From <strong>Purcellville</strong>, take S. 20th Street (611 / Telegraph Springs Road / New Ford Road) to Snickersville Turnpike. Turn Right on Snickersville Turnpike (734). Continue on 734 until it ends in Aldie. Turn Left n Route 50, go through Aldie, the church will be on your left.</p>\r\n', 'Directions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'directions', '', '', '2010-09-24 12:08:17', '2010-09-24 12:08:17', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com', 0, 'page', '', 0),
