(33, 1, '2010-09-22 17:39:02', '2010-09-22 17:39:02', '<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Head of the Church</td>\n<td>Jesus Christ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bishop(s) of the Diocese of Virginia</td>\n<td><a href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Johnston/">Shannon Johnston</a>\n<a title="Bishop Jones" href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Jones/">David Colin Jones</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Rector</td>\n<td>John Thomas Sheehan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Youth Minister</td>\n<td>vacant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2">Vestry</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2">Choir</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Treasurer</td>\n<td>Cate Roche, Monica Hoybach</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Administrative Assistant</td>\n<td>Marjorie Fairbanks</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>', 'Staff', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '30-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:39:02', '2010-09-22 17:39:02', '', 30, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/33', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(34, 1, '2010-09-22 17:41:38', '2010-09-22 17:41:38', 'Contact for pastoral emergencies: (703)728-0355\r\nEmail: jsheehan@aldiechurch.com\r\n\r\nThe Reverend John Thomas Sheehan was called by Our Redeemer as its  first fulltime priest in the 153 year history of the parish. Since his  arrival, the parish has grown and been revitalized. Under his  leadership, the church returned to full parish status in the diocese and  has been self supporting, leaving diocesan aid in 2004.\r\nJohn was ordained a priest in 2001 and received his Masters of Divinity  from Trinity Episcopal School for Ministry in Ambridge, PA. He is  currently pursuing his Doctor of Ministry from Trinity.\r\nBefore joining the priesthood, John worked in various legislative and  political venues in Washington, DC, including the Center for Media and  Public Affairs, the National Republican Senatorial Committee and the  Chamber of Commerce of the United States. But he is most proud of his  work with the Bailey Family Foundation, which provided financial  assistance and scholarships to deserving students.\r\nJohn and his wife, Denise, have three children Ryan, Kerry and Matthew.\r\n\r\nHonk, if you see "Adlie 1"\r\n<img src="http://www.aldiechurch.com/drupal-5.2/files/images/aldie1.jpg" alt="" />', 'John Thomas Sheehan', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'john-thomas-sheehan', '', '', '2010-09-23 20:22:59', '2010-09-23 20:22:59', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(35, 1, '2010-09-22 17:41:28', '2010-09-22 17:41:28', 'Contact for pastoral emergencies: (703)728-0355\nEmail: jsheehan@aldiechurch.com\n\nThe Reverend John Thomas Sheehan was called by Our Redeemer as its  first fulltime priest in the 153 year history of the parish. Since his  arrival, the parish has grown and been revitalized. Under his  leadership, the church returned to full parish status in the diocese and  has been self supporting, leaving diocesan aid in 2004.\nJohn was ordained a priest in 2001 and received his Masters of Divinity  from Trinity Episcopal School for Ministry in Ambridge, PA. He is  currently pursuing his Doctor of Ministry from Trinity.\nBefore joining the priesthood, John worked in various legislative and  political venues in Washington, DC, including the Center for Media and  Public Affairs, the National Republican Senatorial Committee and the  Chamber of Commerce of the United States. But he is most proud of his  work with the Bailey Family Foundation, which provided financial  assistance and scholarships to deserving students.\nJohn and his wife, Denise, have three children Ryan, Kerry and Matthew.\n\n\nHonk, if you see "Adlie 1"\n\n<img src="http://www.aldiechurch.com/drupal-5.2/files/images/SheehanFamily.jpg" alt="" />\n<img src="http://www.aldiechurch.com/drupal-5.2/files/images/aldie1.jpg" alt="" />', 'John Thomas Sheehan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '34-revision', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:41:28', '2010-09-22 17:41:28', '', 34, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/35', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
