(44, 1, '2010-09-22 17:41:38', '2010-09-22 17:41:38', 'Contact for pastoral emergencies: (703)728-0355\r\nEmail: jsheehan@aldiechurch.com\r\n\r\nThe Reverend John Thomas Sheehan was called by Our Redeemer as its  first fulltime priest in the 153 year history of the parish. Since his  arrival, the parish has grown and been revitalized. Under his  leadership, the church returned to full parish status in the diocese and  has been self supporting, leaving diocesan aid in 2004.\r\nJohn was ordained a priest in 2001 and received his Masters of Divinity  from Trinity Episcopal School for Ministry in Ambridge, PA. He is  currently pursuing his Doctor of Ministry from Trinity.\r\nBefore joining the priesthood, John worked in various legislative and  political venues in Washington, DC, including the Center for Media and  Public Affairs, the National Republican Senatorial Committee and the  Chamber of Commerce of the United States. But he is most proud of his  work with the Bailey Family Foundation, which provided financial  assistance and scholarships to deserving students.\r\nJohn and his wife, Denise, have three children Ryan, Kerry and Matthew.\r\n\r\n\r\nHonk, if you see "Adlie 1"\r\n\r\n<img src="http://www.aldiechurch.com/drupal-5.2/files/images/SheehanFamily.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<img src="http://www.aldiechurch.com/drupal-5.2/files/images/aldie1.jpg" alt="" />', 'John Thomas Sheehan', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '34-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:41:38', '2010-09-22 17:41:38', '', 34, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/44', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(45, 1, '2010-09-22 17:51:13', '2010-09-22 17:51:13', 'God loves you. Want to know more? Visit <a href="http://aldie-alpha.com">http://aldie-alpha.com</a> and join us every Wednesday night at 7pm beginning September 22, 2010.', 'Alpha is Coming', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'open', '', 'alpha-is-coming', '', '', '2010-10-25 14:25:55', '2010-10-25 19:25:55', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/?p=45', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(46, 1, '2010-09-22 17:51:10', '2010-09-22 17:51:10', 'God loves you. Want to know more? Visit <a href="http://aldie-alpha.com">http://aldie-alpha.com</a> and join us every Wednesday night at 7pm beginning September 22, 2010.', 'Alpha is Coming', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '45-revision', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:51:10', '2010-09-22 17:51:10', '', 45, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/46', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(47, 1, '2010-09-22 17:54:06', '2010-09-22 17:54:06', 'Part of being disciple is learning the discipline of service. If you''re unsure of how to start, why not start by being an usher?\r\n<!-- more -->\r\nBeing an usher requires no preparation or commitment outside of the service, and yet it is the first contact that most members will have as they join the church. Responsibilities boil down to greeting people with the joy you already have, giving them a bulletin, and bringing up the communion elements after announcements.  It''s easy but important.\r\n\r\nIf you''re ready to sign up, please contact John Sheehan at (703)327-4060.', 'We need ushers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'we-need-ushers', '', '', '2010-09-29 15:37:59', '2010-09-29 15:37:59', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/?p=47', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(48, 1, '2010-09-22 17:53:23', '2010-09-22 17:53:23', 'Part of being disciple is learning the discipline of service. If you''re unsure of how to start, why not start by being an usher?\n\nBeing an usher requires no preparation or commitment outside of the service, and yet it is the first contact that most members will have as they join the church. Responsibilities boil down to greeting people with the joy you already have, giving them a bulletin, and bringing up the communion ements  ', 'We need ushers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '47-revision', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:53:23', '2010-09-22 17:53:23', '', 47, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/48', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(49, 1, '2010-09-22 17:54:06', '2010-09-22 17:54:06', 'Part of being disciple is learning the discipline of service. If you''re unsure of how to start, why not start by being an usher?\r\n\r\nBeing an usher requires no preparation or commitment outside of the service, and yet it is the first contact that most members will have as they join the church. Responsibilities boil down to greeting people with the joy you already have, giving them a bulletin, and bringing up the communion elements after announcements.  It''s easy but important. \r\n\r\nIf you''re ready to sign up, please contact John Sheehan at (703)327-4060.', 'We need ushers', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '47-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 17:54:06', '2010-09-22 17:54:06', '', 47, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/49', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
