rit', 'open', 'open', '', '56-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:00:29', '2010-09-22 18:00:29', '', 56, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/58', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(59, 1, '2010-09-22 18:05:57', '2010-09-22 18:05:57', 'Yes, we provide a free-of-charge nursery using paid staff during the 10am service. There is no child care during the 8am service.\r\n\r\nYou can expect that your infant - 3 year old will be cared for by a competent care giver in a low worker-to-child ratio environment. Please come downstairs and turn into the hallway that leads away from the fellowship hall, through the open door. The nursery will be the first room on the right and has a dutch (half) door with a clear glass paned window and a wide assortment of toys.\r\n\r\nOlder children have Sunday School available, and will join us for Eucharist towards the end of the service. Children in the nursery will remain in the nursery until the parent who dropped them off retrieves them.\r\n\r\nFor the benefit of all children, we ask that if your child has had a fever or significant nasal discharge in the last 24 hours, please do NOT bring them to nursery.  If your child''s feeding time is during the service, please bring a bottle.', 'Do you have childcare?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'do-you-have-childcare', '', '', '2010-09-24 15:05:17', '2010-09-24 15:05:17', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/?p=59', 0, 'post', '', 0),
