(61, 1, '2010-09-22 18:05:57', '2010-09-22 18:05:57', 'Yes, we provide a free-of-charge nursery using paid staff during the 10am service. You can expect that your infant - 3 year old will be cared for by a competent care giver in a low worker-to-child ratio environment. Please come downstairs and turn into the hallway that leads away from the fellowship hall, through the open door. The nursery will be the first room on the right and has a dutch (half) door with a clear glass paned window and a wide assortment of toys.\r\n\r\nOlder children have Sunday School available, and will join us for Eucharist towards the end of the service. Children in the nursery will remain in the nursery until the parent who dropped them off retrieves them.\r\n\r\nFor the benefit of all children, we ask that if your child has had a fever or significant nasal discharge in the last 24 hours, please do NOT bring them to nursery.  If your child''s feeding time is during the service, please bring a bottle.', 'Do you have childcare?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '59-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:05:57', '2010-09-22 18:05:57', '', 59, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/61', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(62, 1, '2010-09-22 18:09:19', '2010-09-22 18:09:19', 'In addition to the nursery, we provide Sunday School for children ages 3 through 12th grade, during the 10am service only.\r\n\r\nChildren ages 3 - 5 are "Lambs" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the section furthest to the left.\r\nChildren in 1st through 3rd grade are "Lions" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the middle section.\r\nChildren in 4th through 6th grade meet in the upstairs office, visible from the fellowship hall.\r\nHigh Schoolers meet in the "Gateway Room," down the hall from the fellowship hall.\r\n\r\nFor questions regarding curriculum, please contact the church office.', 'Do you have programs for my child? for my teenager?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'do-you-have-programs-for-my-child-for-my-teenager', '', '', '2010-09-24 15:04:51', '2010-09-24 15:04:51', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/?p=62', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(63, 1, '2010-09-22 18:08:19', '2010-09-22 18:08:19', 'In addition to the nursery, we provide Sunday School for children ages 3 through 12th grade, during the 10am service only.\n\nChildren ages 3 - 5 are "Lambs" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the section furthest to the left.\nChildren in 1st through 3rd grade are "Lions" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the middle section.\nChildren in 4th', 'Do you have programs for my child? for my teenager?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:08:19', '2010-09-22 18:08:19', '', 62, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/63', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(64, 1, '2010-09-22 18:09:19', '2010-09-22 18:09:19', 'In addition to the nursery, we provide Sunday School for children ages 3 through 12th grade, during the 10am service only.\r\n\r\nChildren ages 3 - 5 are "Lambs" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the section furthest to the left.\r\nChildren in 1st through 3rd grade are "Lions" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the middle section.\r\nChildren in 4th through 6th grade meet in the upstairs office, visible from the fellowship hall.\r\nHigh Schoolers meet in the "Gateway Room," down the hall from the fellowship hall.', 'Do you have programs for my child? for my teenager?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:09:19', '2010-09-22 18:09:19', '', 62, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/64', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(65, 1, '2010-09-22 18:06:07', '2010-09-22 18:06:07', 'Yes, we provide a free-of-charge nursery using paid staff during the 10am service. You can expect that your infant - 3 year old will be cared for by a competent care giver in a low worker-to-child ratio environment. Please come downstairs and turn into the hallway that leads away from the fellowship hall, through the open door. The nursery will be the first room on the right and has a dutch (half) door with a clear glass paned window and a wide assortment of toys.\r\n\r\nOlder children have Sunday School available, and will join us for Eucharist towards the end of the service. Children in the nursery will remain in the nursery until the parent who dropped them off retrieves them.\r\n\r\nFor the benefit of all children, we ask that if your child has had a fever or significant nasal discharge in the last 24 hours, please do NOT bring them to nursery.  If your child''s feeding time is during the service, please bring a bottle.', 'Do you have childcare?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '59-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:06:07', '2010-09-22 18:06:07', '', 59, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/archives/65', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(66, 1, '2010-09-22 18:13:33', '2010-09-22 18:13:33', 'Indeed we do!\r\n\r\nWomen meet weekly on Wednesday mornings at 9:30am in the fellowship hall.\r\n\r\nMen meet monthly on the 2nd Sunday of each month. Contact Michael Hollinger (mcholl@yahoo.com) for an electronic copy of the bible study that we will discuss for the upcoming month. We meet in the Gateway room shorty after the service (but not so shortly that we don''t get a bite or two from coffee hour)\r\n\r\nWednesday evenings are a "co-ed" Bible Study, meeting in the fellowship hall at 7pm.\r\n\r\nAdditional opportunities for discipleship, fellowship, and study are held throughout the year, and are advertised in the announcements.', 'Do you have programs for adults?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'do-you-have-programs-for-adults', '', '', '2010-09-24 15:03:48', '2010-09-24 15:03:48', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch.com/?p=66', 0, 'post', '', 0),
