(105, 1, '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', 'Contact for pastoral emergencies: (703)728-0355\r\nEmail: jsheehan@aldiechurch.com\r\n\r\nThe Reverend John Thomas Sheehan was called by Our Redeemer as its  first fulltime priest in the 153 year history of the parish. Since his  arrival, the parish has grown and been revitalized. Under his  leadership, the church returned to full parish status in the diocese and  has been self supporting, leaving diocesan aid in 2004.\r\nJohn was ordained a priest in 2001 and received his Masters of Divinity  from Trinity Episcopal School for Ministry in Ambridge, PA. He is  currently pursuing his Doctor of Ministry from Trinity.\r\nBefore joining the priesthood, John worked in various legislative and  political venues in Washington, DC, including the Center for Media and  Public Affairs, the National Republican Senatorial Committee and the  Chamber of Commerce of the United States. But he is most proud of his  work with the Bailey Family Foundation, which provided financial  assistance and scholarships to deserving students.\r\nJohn and his wife, Denise, have three children Ryan, Kerry and Matthew.\r\n\r\n\r\nHonk, if you see “Adlie 1?\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '105', '', '', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '', 30, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/?p=105', 5, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '\r\n\r\nHead of the Church\r\nJesus Christ\r\n\r\n\r\nBishop(s) of the Diocese of Virginia\r\nShannon Johnston\r\nDavid Colin Jones\r\n\r\n\r\nRector\r\nJohn Thomas Sheehan\r\n\r\n\r\nYouth Minister\r\nvacant\r\n\r\n\r\nVestry\r\n\r\n\r\nChoir\r\n\r\n\r\nTreasurer\r\nCate Roche, Monica Hoybach\r\n\r\n\r\nAdministrative Assistant\r\nMarjorie Fairbanks\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '106', '', '', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/?p=106', 6, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', 'The Church of Our Redeemer is located on Route 50 (John Mosby Highway) in the village of Aldie at 39518 John Mosby Highway ·  Aldie, VA 20105. The church is 1 mile west of the traffic circle where Route 15 (north to Leesburg, south to Haymarket) and Route 50 (west to Middleburg, east to South Riding) intersect.  For directions, click here or look at the map below.\r\nFrom South Riding, head west on Route 50, past the three traffic circles. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Leesburg, head south on 15, turn right onto Route 50. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Haymarket, I-66, and points south, head north on 15, go 3/4 around the traffic circle onto Route 50 west. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Middleburg and points west, head east on Route 50, past Snickersville Turnpike, and through Aldie. The church will be on your left.', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '107', '', '', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/?p=107', 7, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(108, 1, '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', 'The Church of Our Redeemer meets according to the following schedule:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSUNDAY\r\n\r\n\r\n8am\r\nContemplative Service (no music, no childcare)\r\n\r\n\r\n10am\r\nMain Service – music, childcare, Sunday school\r\n\r\n\r\n11:15am\r\nCoffee Hour\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMen’s Bible Study, after main service 2nd Sunday of each month\r\n\r\n\r\nMONDAY\r\n\r\n\r\n3pm – 7pm\r\nPastor’s Open Door Time.\r\n\r\nWould you like to talk to the rector without scheduling an appointment? This time is specifically set aside for your “interruption!”\r\n\r\n\r\nWEDNESDAY\r\n\r\n\r\n8am\r\nHealing Service (Eucharist) and open discussion of lessons\r\n\r\n\r\n9:30am\r\nWomen’s Bible Study\r\n\r\n\r\n7pm\r\nBible Study\r\n\r\n\r\nTHURSDAY\r\n\r\n\r\n7:30pm\r\nChoir Practice\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '108', '', '', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '2010-09-23 13:55:46', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/?p=108', 8, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(260, 1, '2010-09-28 14:05:17', '2010-09-28 14:05:17', '(Yes, I would upload a file. Note: Eventually, I want to get to the point where I use embedded pdf players, so you can just read through the output directly...)', 'Mar/Apr 2001 [Demo Only]', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-autosave', '', '', '2010-09-28 14:05:17', '2010-09-28 14:05:17', '', 222, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/260', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
