(113, 1, '2010-09-22 19:00:47', '2010-09-22 19:00:47', 'I''m a sucker for a good Christian song and the stories behind them. <a href="http://www.hymnary.org/">http://www.hymnary.org/</a> collects them all, lets you hear them, read them, and get information about the authors and composers who wrote them.', 'Hymnary.org', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '96-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-22 19:00:47', '2010-09-22 19:00:47', '', 96, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/113', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(114, 1, '2010-09-22 18:59:03', '2010-09-22 18:59:03', 'Ever wanted to read the ancient church texts? You know, you may have heard of "Macabees" or "The Didache." Basically, if you know that the church didn''t necessarily start in the 20th Century, you owe it to yourself to read the classics. What you don''t owe is some book publisher lots of money to do it.  The <a href="http://www.ccel.org/">Christian Classics Ethereal Library</a> is an easy way to read the old texts.', 'CCEL.org', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '94-revision-2', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:59:03', '2010-09-22 18:59:03', '', 94, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/114', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(115, 1, '2010-09-22 18:56:41', '2010-09-22 18:56:41', 'C. Michael Patton comes out of Dallas Theological Seminary, and has a passion for training lay people in how to do theology. Check out "Theology Unplugged," a podcast that will teach you how to "do" theology without necessarily going to seminary, and his blog which I think is pretty well done.\r\n\r\nHere''s the link: <a href="http://www.reclaimingthemind.org/blog/">http://www.reclaimingthemind.org/blog/</a>\r\n\r\nMichael.', 'Parchment & Pen', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '89-revision-5', '', '', '2010-09-22 18:56:41', '2010-09-22 18:56:41', '', 89, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/115', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
