(157, 1, '2010-09-23 17:04:44', '2010-09-23 17:04:44', 'The Church of Our Redeemer is located on Route 50 (John Mosby Highway) in the village of Aldie at <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=39518+John+Mosby+Highway,+Aldie,+VA&amp;sll=38.975075,-77.634737&amp;sspn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=39518+John+Mosby+Hwy,+Aldie,+Loudoun,+Virginia+20105&amp;ll=38.975225,-77.636969&amp;spn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;z=16">39518 John Mosby Highway ·  Aldie, VA 20105</a>. The church is 1 mile west of the traffic circle where Route 15 (north to Leesburg, south to Haymarket) and Route 50 (west to Middleburg, east to South Riding) intersect.  For directions, <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;source=s_q&amp;hl=en&amp;geocode=&amp;q=39518+John+Mosby+Highway,+Aldie,+VA&amp;sll=38.975075,-77.634737&amp;sspn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=39518+John+Mosby+Hwy,+Aldie,+Loudoun,+Virginia+20105&amp;ll=38.975225,-77.636969&amp;spn=0.008741,0.022724&amp;z=16">click here</a> or look at the map below.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a rel="attachment wp-att-21" href="http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/about-us-placeholder/directions/directions"><img class="size-full wp-image-21 aligncenter" title="directions" src="../wp-content/uploads/2010/09/directions.png" alt="Directions to Church of Our Redeemer" width="288" height="144" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\nFrom South Riding, head west on Route 50, past the three traffic circles. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Leesburg, head south on 15, turn right onto Route 50. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Haymarket, I-66, and points south, head north on 15, go 3/4 around the traffic circle onto Route 50 west. The church will be on your right.\r\nFrom Middleburg and points west, head east on Route 50, past Snickersville Turnpike, and through Aldie. The church will be on your left.\r\n\r\nFrom Purcellville, take S. 20th Street (611 / Telegraph Springs Road / New Ford Road) to Snickersville Turnpike. Turn Right on Snickersville Turnpike (734). Continue on 734 until it ends in Aldie. Turn Left n Route 50, go through Aldie, the church will be on your left.', 'Directions', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '16-revision-19', '', '', '2010-09-23 17:04:44', '2010-09-23 17:04:44', '', 16, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/157', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2010-09-23 16:00:20', '2010-09-23 16:00:20', 'The Church of Our Redeemer meets according to the following schedule:\r\n<table border="0" width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>SUNDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">8am</td>\r\n<td>Contemplative Service (no music, no childcare)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>10am</td>\r\n<td>Main Service - music, childcare, Sunday school</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>11:15am</td>\r\n<td>Coffee Hour</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td>Men''s Bible Study, after main service 2nd Sunday of each month</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>MONDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">3pm - 7pm</td>\r\n<td>Pastor''s Scheuled Open Door</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>WEDNESDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">8am</td>\r\n<td>Healing Service (Eucharist) and open discussion of lessons</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">9:30am</td>\r\n<td>Women''s Bible Study</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">7pm</td>\r\n<td>Bible Study</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>THURSDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">7:30pm</td>\r\n<td>Choir Practice</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Schedule of Services', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-11', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:00:20', '2010-09-23 16:00:20', '', 5, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/146', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'We practice what is called ''Open Communion.'' Basically we figure you''re an adult, and know that this is a solemn ceremony memorializing the sacrifice that Jesus made on our behalf. For that reason, both we and <a href="http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/?search=1%20Corinthians%2011:27-29&amp;version=NLT">Scripture</a> suggest you not take it lightly, but we do encourage <em>all</em> baptised Christians (regardless of denomination) to join.  Typically, we suggest that younger children should be confirmed (usually around the age of 11 or 12) before actually taking the elements, but again, we trust you to make that decision.\r\n\r\nIf for any reason you are not comfortable taking communion, please come forward anyway to receive a blessing. If you are concerned about catching anything, you needn''t - our priest uses rubbing alcohol to clean his hands before serving, and the vessels are thoroughly washed after every service.  Finally, if you would prefer, a separate cup for continction (dipping) is available.\r\n\r\n<em><em>So, what is communion?</em></em> If you were observing it like an anthropologist, this is what you''d see:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The Priest pours a cup of wine and prays over a piece of bread.</li>\r\n	<li>Everybody in the church will get out of their seats (by rows), and stand in line until there is space available to kneel at the altar.</li>\r\n	<li>When you get to the altar, if you do NOT want to take the elements, simply cross your hands over your chest, and the priest will give you a blessing. You can simply leave at this point.</li>\r\n	<li>Those receiving communion will hold their hand out for the bread, which the priest will place on the hand. One can either eat the bread or wait until the cup comes and dip it.</li>\r\n	<li>The cup of wine is then brought, and you either take a sip or dip your bread.</li>\r\n	<li>People then return to their seat.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nIt''s not that scary. What is happening, however, is that we are playing out the "Last Supper," the last passover which Jesus celebrated, the night before he was sentenced to death on the cross. While the ceremony he was celebrating remembered the Israelites being rescued from Egypt even as the Egyptians were being killed, Jesus used the ceremony to show that he was rescuing his followers from Sin, and would die in the process.\r\n\r\nIf you want to know more, please contact our rector', 'How do you do communion?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '79-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 79, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/213', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(147, 1, '2010-09-23 16:28:36', '2010-09-23 16:28:36', '<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Head of the Church</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jesus">Jesus Christ</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bishop(s) of the Diocese of Virginia</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Johnston/">Shannon Johnston</a>\r\n<a title="Bishop Jones" href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Jones/">David Colin Jones</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Rector</td>\r\n<td><a href="john-thomas-sheehan">John Thomas Sheehan</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Youth Minister</td>\r\n<td>vacant</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><a href="vestry">Vestry</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><a href="choir">Choir</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Treasurer</td>\r\n<td>Cate Roche,\r\nMonica Hoybach</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Administrative Assistant</td>\r\n<td>Marjorie Fairbanks</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Staff', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '30-revision-8', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:28:36', '2010-09-23 16:28:36', '', 30, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/147', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
