(209, 1, '2010-09-24 14:06:18', '2010-09-24 14:06:18', 'The Church Office is open 9am - 6pm, Monday - Thursday.\r\nYou can reach us at (703) 327-4060.\r\n\r\nFor pastoral emergencies, call (703)728-0355.\r\nIf you would like to visit with the pastor, but feel uncomfortable making an appointment, please stop by on Mondays from 3-7, where the rector holds "Open Door." The purpose of Open Door is specifically to schedule a time for ''drop-in visits,'' for those who do not wish to make an appointment. Our rector is happy to make appointments at other times if that is more convenient.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to contact us via email, please address correspondance to:\r\n\r\nadmin@aldiechurch.com\r\n\r\nrector@aldiechurch.com', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '149-autosave', '', '', '2010-09-24 14:06:18', '2010-09-24 14:06:18', '', 149, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/209', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(210, 1, '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', 'The Church Office is open 9am - 6pm, Monday - Thursday.\r\nYou can reach us at (703) 327-4060.\r\n\r\nFor pastoral emergencies, call (703)728-0355.\r\nIf you would like to visit with the pastor, but feel uncomfortable making an appointment, please stop by on Mondays from 3-7, where the rector holds "Open Door." The purpose of Open Door is specifically to schedule a time for ''drop-in visits,'' for those who do not wish to make an appointment. Our rector is happy to make appointments at other times if that is more convenient.', 'Contact Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '149-revision-5', '', '', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '', 149, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/210', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(211, 1, '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Head of the Church</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jesus">Jesus Christ</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Bishop(s) of the Diocese of Virginia</td>\r\n<td><a href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Johnston/">Shannon Johnston</a>\r\n<a title="Bishop Jones" href="http://www.thediocese.net/Diocesan_Community/Bishops/Bishops_Biographies_/Bishop_Jones/">David Colin Jones</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Rector</td>\r\n<td><a href="john-thomas-sheehan">John Thomas Sheehan</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Youth Minister</td>\r\n<td>vacant</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><a href="vestry">Vestry</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><a href="choir">Choir</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Treasurer</td>\r\n<td>Cate Roche,\r\nMonica Hoybach</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Administrative Assistant</td>\r\n<td>Marjorie Fairbanks</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Staff', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '30-revision-10', '', '', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '', 30, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/211', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(212, 1, '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', 'The Church of Our Redeemer meets according to the following schedule:\r\n<table border="0" width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>SUNDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">8am</td>\r\n<td>Contemplative Service (no music, no childcare)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>10am</td>\r\n<td>Main Service - music, childcare, Sunday school</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>11:15am</td>\r\n<td>Coffee Hour</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td>Men''s Bible Study, after main service 2nd Sunday of each month</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>MONDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">3pm - 7pm</td>\r\n<td>Pastor''s Scheuled Open Door</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>WEDNESDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">8am</td>\r\n<td>Healing Service (Eucharist) and open discussion of lessons</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">9:30am</td>\r\n<td>Women''s Bible Study</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">7pm</td>\r\n<td>Bible Study</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="2">\r\n<h3>THURSDAY</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="20%">7:30pm</td>\r\n<td>Choir Practice</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'Schedule of Services', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-13', '', '', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '2010-09-23 17:28:20', '', 5, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/212', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'Clothes. We definately recommend clothes at our services. :)\r\n\r\nBeyond that, Church of Our Redeemer is not a stuffy place. We don''t wear hats, and only a few people wear suits. Our rector and the people serving up front wear robes, but only in the service.  We''re not going to judge you by what you wear.\r\n\r\nThat said, some people would like to know how "everybody else dresses." If it''s helpful to say, ''business casual,'' then go with that answer.', 'What should I wear?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '77-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 77, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/214', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(215, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'Church of Our Redeemer conducts services according the (episcopal) <em>1979 Book of Common Prayer</em> in a ''low church'' style. If you grew up in an Anglican tradition, the forms will be familiar.  If like many of us in the church, however, you didn''t, here''s a few hints.\r\n\r\n1.The entire service is printed in the bulletin each week, and for the most part, you just follow along. Whenever the bulletin says, ''People,'' you read off what it says :)\r\n\r\n2. The order of service usually compromises the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>an opening prayer and song</li>\r\n	<li>readings from the Old Testament, the Psalms, the Epistles, and a reading from the Gospels (during which we typically stand)</li>\r\n	<li>a sermon,usually about 20 minutes or so</li>\r\n	<li>a time of creedal affirmation and prayer</li>\r\n	<li>a time of "Peace" in which we greet one another</li>\r\n	<li>a time of Eucharist (Communion) in which we celebrate the Lord''s Last Supper</li>\r\n	<li>and coffee hour, in which we fellowship with our church</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n3. What if I get lost in the service?\r\n\r\nDon''t worry, we all do. Just peek over at your neighbor, and they''ll help you out.', 'What should I expect in a service at Church of Our Redeemer?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '74-revision-4', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 74, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/215', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(216, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'There is music and a choir at the 10am service. We choose a wide variety of modern and classical music from <em>The Hymnal 1982, Renew</em>, and<em> Lift Every Voice and Sing</em>.We have enough old Baptists in our congregation to ensure that a wide variety of the classics get sung.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, we present a children''s christmas concert during Advent.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to join the choir, you are invited to show up at practice on Thursday nights at 7:30.', 'What do you do for music?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '68-revision-6', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 68, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/216', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(217, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'Indeed we do!\r\n\r\nWomen meet weekly on Wednesday mornings at 9:30am in the fellowship hall.\r\n\r\nMen meet monthly on the 2nd Sunday of each month. Contact Michael Hollinger (mcholl@yahoo.com) for an electronic copy of the bible study that we will discuss for the upcoming month. We meet in the Gateway room shorty after the service (but not so shortly that we don''t get a bite or two from coffee hour)\r\n\r\nWednesday evenings are a "co-ed" Bible Study, meeting in the fellowship hall at 7pm.\r\n\r\nAdditional opportunities for discipleship, fellowship, and study are held throughout the year, and are advertised in the announcements.', 'Do you have programs for adults?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '66-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 66, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/217', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(218, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'In addition to the nursery, we provide Sunday School for children ages 3 through 12th grade, during the 10am service only.\r\n\r\nChildren ages 3 - 5 are "Lambs" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the section furthest to the left.\r\nChildren in 1st through 3rd grade are "Lions" and meet in the fellowship hall, in the middle section.\r\nChildren in 4th through 6th grade meet in the upstairs office, visible from the fellowship hall.\r\nHigh Schoolers meet in the "Gateway Room," down the hall from the fellowship hall.\r\n\r\nFor questions regarding curriculum, please contact the church office.', 'Do you have programs for my child? for my teenager?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '62-revision-4', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 62, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/218', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(219, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'Yes, we provide a free-of-charge nursery using paid staff during the 10am service. There is no child care during the 8am service.\r\n\r\nYou can expect that your infant - 3 year old will be cared for by a competent care giver in a low worker-to-child ratio environment. Please come downstairs and turn into the hallway that leads away from the fellowship hall, through the open door. The nursery will be the first room on the right and has a dutch (half) door with a clear glass paned window and a wide assortment of toys.\r\n\r\nOlder children have Sunday School available, and will join us for Eucharist towards the end of the service. Children in the nursery will remain in the nursery until the parent who dropped them off retrieves them.\r\n\r\nFor the benefit of all children, we ask that if your child has had a fever or significant nasal discharge in the last 24 hours, please do NOT bring them to nursery.  If your child''s feeding time is during the service, please bring a bottle.', 'Do you have childcare?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '59-revision-5', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 59, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/219', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'OUR MISSION:\r\n\r\nTo serve God, to exalt Jesus Christ our Lord and Savior, to proclaim His Word.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSTATEMENT OF FAITH:\r\n\r\nWe affirm our belief in historic Christianity as revealed in the Scriptures and\r\nsummarized in the three Creeds (the <a href=''http://www.creeds.net/ancient/apostles.htm''>Apostles</a>, the <a href=''http://www.creeds.net/ancient/nicene.htm''>Nicene</a>, and the <a href=''http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Athanasian_Creed''>Athanasian</a>)\r\nand the <a href=''http://anglicansonline.org/basics/thirty-nine_articles.html''>Thirty-Nine Articles</a>. We recognize the need to proclaim and to reaffirm\r\nthe following beliefs:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nARTICLE 1 - The Holy Trinity\r\n\r\nThe mystery of the Holy Trinity, namely, that the one God exists eternally in\r\nthe three persons: Father, Son and Holy Spirit; and has so revealed himself to\r\nus in the Gospel.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE II - The Lord Jesus Christ\r\n\r\nThe full deity and full humanity of our Lord Jesus Christ, God Incarnate, who\r\nby reason of his birth of the Virgin Mary, sinless life, atoning death, bodily\r\nresurrection, glorious ascension and triumphant reign, is the only Mediator\r\nbetween God and man.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE III - The Holy Scriptures\r\n\r\nThe trustworthiness of the canonical books of the Old and New Testaments as\r\n“God’s Word written,” which contain all things necessary for salvation, teach\r\nGod’s will for his world, and have supreme authority for faith, life and the\r\ncontinuous renewal and reform of the Church.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE IV - Justification and Sanctification\r\n\r\nThe justification of the repenting and believing sinner as God’s gracious act\r\nof declaring him righteous on the ground of the reconciling death of Christ,\r\nwho suffered in our place and rose again for us; and sanctification as the\r\ngracious continuing activity of the Holy Spirit in the justified believer,\r\nperfecting his repentance, nurturing the new life implanted within him,\r\ntransforming him into Christ’s image, and enabling him to do good works in the\r\nworld.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE V - The Christian Church\r\n\r\nThe Church as the Body of Christ, whose members belong to the new humanity, are\r\ncalled to live in the world in the power of the Spirit, worshiping God,\r\nconfessing his truth, proclaiming Christ, supporting one another in love and\r\ngiving themselves in sacrificial service to those in need.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE VI - Spiritual Gifts and Ministry\r\n\r\nThe calling of all Christians to exercise their God-given gifts in ministry,\r\nand to work, witness, and suffer for Christ; together with the particular\r\ncalling of ordained ministers, who, by preaching, teaching and pastoral care,\r\nare to equip God’s people for his service, and to present them mature in\r\nChrist.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE VII - The Gospel Sacraments\r\n\r\nThe sacraments of Baptism and Holy Communion as “visible words” which proclaim\r\nthe Gospel, and are means of grace by which faith is quickened and\r\nstrengthened.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn particular, the significance of the Lord’s Supper as a communion in the Body\r\nand Blood of Christ, who offers himself to us in the action of this sacrament,\r\nso that by faith we may feed on him in our hearts and offer ourselves to him in\r\ngratitude for our salvation through his cross; Also, the openness of the Lord’s\r\nTable as the place where all baptized believers, being one in Christ, are free\r\nto celebrate their common salvation in the Lord, and to express their common\r\ndevotion to his person and his service.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nARTICLE VIII - The Return of Christ\r\n\r\nThe personal return in glory of our Lord Jesus Christ at the end of this age\r\nfor the resurrection of the dead, some to life, some to condemnation, for the\r\nglorification of his Church, and for the renewal of the whole creation.', 'What do you believe?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '56-revision-4', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 56, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/220', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(221, 1, '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', 'Mostly, you just show up :) We don''t carry badges that say "Episcopal" and "Other."\r\n\r\nBeyond that, if you officially want to be an Episcopalian, you must either be baptised or transfer from another church, and be "received" by the Bishop during his yearly visit. For details, please contact the church at (703)327-4060.', 'How do I join?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '81-revision-3', '', '', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '2010-09-23 16:01:02', '', 81, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/221', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(222, 1, '2010-09-24 16:26:33', '2010-09-24 16:26:33', '(Yes, I would upload a file. Note: Eventually, I want to get to the point where I use embedded pdf players, so you can just read through the output directly...)', 'Mar/Apr 2001 [Demo Only]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'marapr-2001-demo-only', '', '', '2010-09-24 16:26:33', '2010-09-24 16:26:33', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/?p=222', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(223, 1, '2010-09-24 16:26:01', '2010-09-24 16:26:01', '(Yes, I would upload a file. Note: Eventually, I want to get to the point where I use embedded pdf players, so you can just read through the output directly...)', 'Mar/Apr 2001 [Demo Only]', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '222-revision', '', '', '2010-09-24 16:26:01', '2010-09-24 16:26:01', '', 222, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/223', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(224, 1, '2010-09-23 18:14:57', '2010-09-23 18:14:57', '<div id="prayer">\r\n\r\nLord Jesus, we pray that you would give us\r\n\r\n<a href="/aldiechurch/sermons">ears to hear</a>, <a href="/aldiechurch/archives/category/community">hearts to love</a>, and <a href="/aldiechurch/archives/category/church/ann">wills devoted to serve</a>.\r\n\r\nThat in the days to come, this congregation would be known, not for our glory, but for yours alone.\r\n\r\nThat this place would be an oasis, a place where people come to find out about you, where lives are straightened out and made whole;\r\n\r\na place where people find the peace that passes all understanding.\r\n\r\nGive us, we pray, a heart to desire these things above all else we pray. We pray through Jesus Christ. Amen\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '176-revision-4', '', '', '2010-09-23 18:14:57', '2010-09-23 18:14:57', '', 176, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/archives/224', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(239, 1, '2010-09-26 12:13:59', '2010-09-26 12:13:59', '[caption id="attachment_240" align="alignnone" width="300" caption="39518 John Mosby Highway; Aldie, VA 20105"]<a rel="attachment wp-att-240" href="http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/building/large_church2"><img class="size-medium wp-image-240" title="Our Building" src="http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/large_church2-300x198.jpg" alt="Church of Our Redeemer Building" width="300" height="198" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\nLike any church, we''re proud of our building, but we are clear on this - a church is a community of people, not a facility. As you browse the pictures, we hope you''ll find these useful in navigating our facility, and hope you''ll feel as at home here as we do.\r\n\r\nA realtor member of the church created a panaromic walkthrough f the church that can be viewed <a href="http://www.realtourvision.com/tour/BU/tour.view.new.php?utl=BU-7240-Z6R619-01">here</a>.', 'Our Facility', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'building', '', '', '2010-09-28 17:18:14', '2010-09-28 17:18:14', '', 0, 'http://doverknoll.com/aldiechurch', 0, 'page', '', 0),
